<%- include("partials/header") -%>

<section class="lightSection">
  <div>
    <h1 class="title">Extend Your Trip</h1>

    <div class="mb-3">
      <div class="swingvasion-box">
        <div class="swingvasion-details">
          <div class="m-4">
            <h3 class="p-0 mt-4">Southern Lights Swing + Swingvasion</h3>
            <p>
              Make the most of your journey by attending two incredible West
              Coast Swing events on back-to-back weekends. Start your adventure
              in Hobart at Southern Lights Swing, then explore New Zealand
              before finishing with another unforgettable weekend of dancing at
              Swingvasion in Wellington.
            </p>
            <p>
              Learn more about Southern Lights Swing:
              <a target="_blank" href="https://www.southernlightsswing.com.au/">
                www.southernlightsswing.com.au
              </a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-3">
      <div class="swingvasion-box">
        <div class="swingvasion-details">
          <div class="m-4">
            <h2>Choose Your Adventure</h2>
            <p>
              Whether you're combining your trip with Southern Lights Swing or
              simply exploring New Zealand, these itineraries will help you make
              the most of your adventure.
            </p>

            <h3 class="p-0 mt-4">1: The Dance & Discovery Tour</h3>
            <p>
              Perfect for travellers who want to maximise their dancing while
              still experiencing a taste of New Zealand at a relaxed pace.
              Connect with the West Coast Swing communities in Hobart and
              Auckland, then use your time between events to explore some of the
              North Island’s most iconic destinations before arriving in
              Wellington.
            </p>

            <h3 class="p-0 mt-4">2: The Classic Kiwi Road Trip</h3>
            <p>
              Perfect for visitors who want to experience more of New Zealand by
              road. Best suited to a self-drive itinerary, this journey takes
              you through rolling farmland, geothermal areas, volcanic plateau
              and lake country, with plenty of opportunities to stop and explore
              as the landscape changes along the way.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-3">
      <div class="swingvasion-box">
        <div class="swingvasion-details">
          <div class="m-4">
            <h3 class="p-0 mt-4">The Dance & Discovery Tour</h3>

            <div class="itinerary-timeline">
              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Monday 1 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">Hobart</h5>
                <p>
                  After an incredible weekend at Southern Lights Swing, spend
                  the day hanging out with new and existing dance friends,
                  before wrapping up your time in Tasmania with a night dancing
                  with the local community at the
                  <a
                    href="https://www.instagram.com/swingdancecollective/"
                    target="_blank"
                    >Swing Dance Collective</a
                  >.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Tuesday 2 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">Hobart -> Auckland</h5>
                <p>
                  Fly from Hobart to Auckland and spend the afternoon exploring
                  New Zealand's largest city. Popular options include the
                  waterfront, Viaduct Harbour, and a trip to Mount Eden.
                </p>
                <p>
                  In the evening, join the Auckland West Coast Swing community
                  at
                  <a href="https://www.streetswing.co.nz/" target="_blank"
                    >Street Swing</a
                  >
                  for their Tuesday night classes and social.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Wednesday 3 - Thursday 4 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">
                  Choose your own adventure! Explore an iconic part ot the upper
                  North Island.
                </h5>
                <p>
                  Book a day trip or two to get out of the city. Popular options
                  include:
                </p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Hobbiton</strong> - Step into Middle-earth with a
                    visit to the world-famous Hobbiton Movie Set. (Note:
                    important to book tickets well in advance!)
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Waitomo</strong> - Experience the magical glowworm
                    caves.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Waiheke Island</strong> - For wine tasting and
                    beaches.
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>Get out of the city for an overnight adventure:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Rotorua</strong> - Discover bubbling mud pools,
                    geothermal parks, redwood forests and Māori cultural
                    experiences.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Coromandel Peninsula</strong> - Escape to beautiful
                    beaches, coastal scenery and iconic spots like Cathedral
                    Cove and hot water beach.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Friday 5 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">Wellington</h5>
                <p>
                  Fly to Wellington on Friday morning (1hour flight). Spend some
                  time exploring Wellington's cafés, waterfront or Te Papa
                  before Swingvasion begins that afternoon.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-3">
      <div class="swingvasion-box">
        <div class="swingvasion-details">
          <div class="m-4">
            <h3 class="p-0 mt-4">The Classic North Island Road Trip</h3>

            <div class="summary-box">
              <strong>Transport:</strong>

              <ul>
                <li>
                  We recommend hiring a rental car for this journey - this is
                  the easiest and most flexible way to explore the route at your
                  own pace. Hire operators allow for pick up in Auckland and
                  drop off in Wellington.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="itinerary-timeline">
              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Monday 1 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">Hobart -> Auckland</h5>
                <p>
                  Fly from Hobart to Auckland and spend the afternoon exploring
                  New Zealand's largest city. Popular options include the
                  waterfront, Viaduct Harbour, and a trip to Mount Eden.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Tuesday 2 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">
                  Auckland -> Hobbiton -> Rotorua
                </h5>
                <p>
                  Travel from Auckland to Hobbiton (2hrs) and then on to Rotorua
                  (1hr), enjoying the rolling green hills of the Waikato and the
                  geothermal heartland of the Bay of Plenty.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Wednesday 3 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">Rotorua</h5>
                <p>Spend the day discovering Rotorua - options include:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Wai-O-Tapu Thermal Wonderland</li>
                  <li>Redwoods Whakarewarewa Forest</li>
                  <li>Māori cultural experiences</li>
                  <li>
                    Adventure activities such as ziplining or mountain biking
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Thursday 4 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">
                  Rotorua -> Taupō -> Wellington
                </h5>
                <p>
                  Travel south through the dramatic landscapes of the central
                  North Island, stopping in Taupō to enjoy the lakefront or
                  visit the spectacular Huka Falls, and drive through the
                  breathtaking Tongariro National Park on your way to Wellington
                  (~5½ hours).
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="itinerary-card">
                <h4 class="itinerary-date">Friday 5 March</h4>
                <h5 class="itinerary-location">Wellington</h5>
                <p>
                  Spend the morning exploring Wellington's cafés, waterfront or
                  Te Papa before Swingvasion begins that afternoon.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-3">
      <div class="swingvasion-box">
        <div class="swingvasion-details">
          <div class="m-4">
            <h3 class="p-0 mt-4">Need More Inspiration?</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <a href="/places-to-explore">Explore Wellington</a> - Things to
                see and do in the capital
              </li>
              <li>
                <a target="_blank" href="https://www.newzealand.com/nz/">
                  New Zealand Tourism</a
                >
                - Official tourism site with travel ideas across the country
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include("partials/footer") -%>
